{"scriptures":{"scriptures":[{"chapter":4,"paragraph":27,"verse":1,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004001,"content":"Now Adam knew Eve his wife, and she conceived and bore Cain, saying, \"I have gotten<footnote><i class=\"catch-word\">Cain</i> sounds like the Hebrew for <i class=\"catch-word\">gotten</i></footnote> a man with the help of the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span>. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":27,"verse":2,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004002,"content":"And again, she bore his brother Abel. Now Abel was a keeper of sheep, and Cain a worker of the ground.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":27,"verse":3,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004003,"content":"In the course of time Cain brought to the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> an offering of <crossref let=\"u\" cid=\"c01004003.1\"/>the fruit of the ground,","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":27,"verse":4,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004004,"content":"and Abel also brought of <crossref let=\"v\" cid=\"c01004004.1\"/>the firstborn of his flock and of their fat portions. And the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> <crossref let=\"w\" cid=\"c01004004.2\"/>had regard for Abel and his offering,","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":27,"verse":5,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004005,"content":"but <crossref let=\"x\" cid=\"c01004005.1\"/>for Cain and his offering he had no regard. So Cain was very angry, and his face fell.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":27,"verse":6,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004006,"content":"The <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> said to Cain, \"Why are you angry, and why has your face fallen?","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":27,"verse":7,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004007,"content":"<crossref let=\"y\" cid=\"c01004007.1\"/>If you do well, will you not be accepted?<footnote>Hebrew <i><span class=\"catch-word\">will</span> there not be a lifting up</i> [of your face]?</footnote> And if you do not do well, sin is crouching at the door. <crossref let=\"z\" cid=\"c01004007.2\"/>Its desire is for<footnote>Or <i>against</i></footnote> you, but you must rule over it. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":28,"verse":8,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004008,"content":"Cain spoke to Abel his brother. <footnote>Hebrew; Samaritan, Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate add <i>Let us go out to the field</i></footnote> And when they were in the field, Cain rose up against his brother Abel and <crossref let=\"a\" cid=\"c01004008.1\"/>killed him.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":28,"verse":9,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004009,"content":"Then the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> said to Cain, \"Where is Abel your brother?\" He said, <crossref let=\"b\" cid=\"c01004009.1\"/>\"I do not know; am I my brother's keeper?\"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":28,"verse":10,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004010,"content":"And the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> said, \"What have you done? The voice of your brother's blood <crossref let=\"c\" cid=\"c01004010.1\"/>is crying to me from the ground.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":28,"verse":11,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004011,"content":"And now <crossref let=\"d\" cid=\"c01004011.1\"/>you are cursed from the ground, which has opened its mouth to receive your brother's blood from your hand.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":28,"verse":12,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004012,"content":"When you work the ground, it shall no longer yield to you its strength. You shall be a fugitive and a wanderer on the earth. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":28,"verse":13,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004013,"content":"Cain said to the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span>, \"My <crossref let=\"e\" cid=\"c01004013.1\"/>punishment is greater than I can bear. <footnote>Or <i>My guilt is too great to bear</i></footnote>","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":28,"verse":14,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004014,"content":"Behold, <crossref let=\"f\" cid=\"c01004014.1\"/>you have driven me today away from the ground, and <crossref let=\"g\" cid=\"c01004014.2\"/>from your face I shall be hidden. I shall be a fugitive and a wanderer on the earth, <crossref let=\"h\" cid=\"c01004014.3\"/>and whoever finds me will kill me. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":28,"verse":15,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004015,"content":"Then the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> said to him, \"Not so! If anyone kills Cain, vengeance shall be taken on him <crossref let=\"i\" cid=\"c01004015.1\"/>sevenfold. \" And the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> <crossref let=\"j\" cid=\"c01004015.2\"/>put a mark on Cain, lest any who found him should attack him.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":28,"verse":16,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004016,"content":"Then Cain went away from the presence of the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> and settled in the land of Nod,<footnote><i class=\"catch-word\">Nod</i> means <i>wandering</i></footnote> east of Eden.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":29,"verse":17,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004017,"content":"Cain knew his wife, and she conceived and bore Enoch. When he built a city, he called the name of the city after the name of his son, Enoch.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":29,"verse":18,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004018,"content":"To Enoch was born Irad, and Irad fathered Mehujael, and Mehujael fathered Methushael, and Methushael fathered Lamech.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":29,"verse":19,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004019,"content":"And Lamech took two wives. The name of the one was Adah, and the name of the other Zillah.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":29,"verse":20,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004020,"content":"Adah bore Jabal; he was the father of those who dwell in tents and have livestock.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":29,"verse":21,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004021,"content":"His brother's name was Jubal; he was the father of all those who play the lyre and pipe.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":29,"verse":22,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004022,"content":"Zillah also bore Tubal-cain; he was the forger of all instruments of bronze and iron. The sister of Tubal-cain was Naamah.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":30,"verse":23,"section_id":5,"block":7,"verse_id":1004023,"content":"Lamech said to his wives:\"Adah and Zillah, hear my voice;<br/>you wives of Lamech, listen to what I say:<br/>I have killed a man for wounding me,<br/>a young man for striking me. <br/>","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":30,"verse":24,"section_id":5,"block":7,"verse_id":1004024,"content":"<crossref let=\"k\" cid=\"c01004024.1\"/>If Cain's revenge is sevenfold,<br/>then Lamech's is seventy-sevenfold. \"<br/>","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":31,"verse":25,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004025,"content":"And Adam knew his wife again, and she bore a son and called his name Seth, for she said, \"God has appointed<footnote><i class=\"catch-word\">Seth</i> sounds like the Hebrew for <i>he appointed</i></footnote> for me another offspring instead of Abel, for Cain killed him. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"},{"chapter":4,"paragraph":31,"verse":26,"section_id":5,"block":null,"verse_id":1004026,"content":"To <crossref let=\"l\" cid=\"c01004026.1\"/>Seth also a son was born, and he called his name <crossref let=\"m\" cid=\"c01004026.2\"/>Enosh. At that time people began <crossref let=\"n\" cid=\"c01004026.3\"/>to call upon the name of the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span>. <end-chapter/>","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Cain and Abel"}],"x_refs":{"c01004007.2":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"3:16","start_ref_id":1003016,"verse_id":1004007,"letter_id":"z"}],"c01004008.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Matt. 23:35","start_ref_id":40023035,"verse_id":1004008,"letter_id":"a"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Heb. 12:24","start_ref_id":58012024,"verse_id":1004008,"letter_id":"a"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"1 John 3:12","start_ref_id":62003012,"verse_id":1004008,"letter_id":"a"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Jude 11","start_ref_id":65001011,"verse_id":1004008,"letter_id":"a"}],"c01004009.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"John 8:44","start_ref_id":43008044,"verse_id":1004009,"letter_id":"b"}],"c01004024.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"15","start_ref_id":1004015,"verse_id":1004024,"letter_id":"k"}],"c01004010.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Heb. 12:24","start_ref_id":58012024,"verse_id":1004010,"letter_id":"c"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Rev. 6:10","start_ref_id":66006010,"verse_id":1004010,"letter_id":"c"}],"c01004011.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Deut. 27:24","start_ref_id":5027024,"verse_id":1004011,"letter_id":"d"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Num. 35:33","start_ref_id":4035033,"verse_id":1004011,"letter_id":"d"}],"c01